us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FrameVector2DReadOnly

  • All Superinterfaces:
    FrameTuple2DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Tuple2DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Vector2DReadOnly
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FixedFrameVector2DBasics, FrameVector2DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameVector2D

    public interface FrameVector2DReadOnly
extends us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Vector2DReadOnly, FrameTuple2DReadOnly
    Read-only interface for a 2D vector expressed in a given reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Vector2DReadOnly, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FrameVector2DReadOnly. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on vectors occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FrameVector2DReadOnly extends Vector2DReadOnly, it is compatible with methods only requiring Vector2DReadOnly. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FrameVector2DReadOnly.

    • Method Detail

      • dot

        default double dot(FrameVector2DReadOnly other)
        Calculates and returns the value of the dot product of this frame vector with other.

        For instance, the dot product of two vectors p and q is defined as:
        p . q = ∑i=1:2(pi * qi)

        Parameters:
        other - the other frame vector used for the dot product. Not modified.
        Returns:
        the value of the dot product.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same frame as this.

      • angle

        default double angle(FrameVector2DReadOnly other)
        Calculates and returns the angle in radians from this frame vector to other.

        The computed angle is in the range [-pi; pi].

        Parameters:
        other - the other frame vector used to compute the angle. Not modified.
        Returns:
        the value of the angle from this frame vector to other.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same frame as this.

      • cross

        default double cross(FrameTuple2DReadOnly tuple)
        Calculates and returns the value of the cross product of this frame vector with tuple.
        Parameters:
        tuple - the second term in the cross product. Not modified.
        Returns:
        the value of the cross product.

      • geometricallyEquals

        default boolean geometricallyEquals(FrameVector2DReadOnly other,
                                    double epsilon)
        Compares this to other to determine if the two frame vectors are geometrically similar, i.e. the length of the distance between them is less than or equal to epsilon.
        Parameters:
        other - the frame vector to compare to. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance of the comparison.
        Returns:
        true if the two frame vectors represent the same geometry, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same reference frame as this.
